raw_data.title: Network Engineer II
raw_data.description: Performs configuration tasks using written procedures and reporting requirements. Evaluates hardware and software; provides technical expertise for performance and configuration of networks. Analyzes network requirements systems and provides a written recommendation of solutions. Troubleshoots and install network components. Submit written recommendations for design, development, testing, and implementation.

raw_data.title: Network Engineer III
raw_data.description: Evaluates hardware and software; provides technical expertise for performance and configuration of networks; provides technical leadership in the integration and test of complex large scale computer integrated networks; schedules conversions and cutovers; oversees network control center; supervises maintenance of systems; coordinates with all responsible users and sites; and supervises staff.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Translates technical and/or non-technical requirements into specific systems, applications or process designs for complex IT systems, solutions, and integrating architecture. May include analysis of transition planning, intelligence information requirements, and may develop architecture baselines. SME disciplines include but are not limited to: ITIL/ITSM process planning; IT certifications (i.e. CISCO, CCNA, VoIP); and Cyber (Architecture, Policy, Forensics, Penetration Testing). Provides process planning, strategy, design and transition activities; process, tools, organization and information work products guide creation; metric development and implementation. Leads development of integration, migration plans/schedules. Acts as an advocate for the client as the ultimate authority on the architecture designed to address client complex IT problems. Often project-based, sometimes working at customer sites. Supports large IT process improvements or systems analysis for missions, systems, and fiscal requirements.

raw_data.title: System Administrator II
raw_data.description: Perform system capacity analysis and planning and ensures functionality of system links. Perform configuration management and documentation of network and system topologies. Prepare technical implementation plans that provide integrated solutions, including actions, milestones, timelines, and critical paths required for complete solutions. Plan, organize, and document complex system design activities and configure systems .Prepare equipment for transport and conduct activities to accomplish the transport of system equipment to and from sites, track the status of the transport, and coordinate receipt of delivery at end sites. Coordinate with the appropriate property custodians as equipment is received, relocated, disposed, or replaced under a maintenance agreement

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer IV
raw_data.description: Designs and performs high-level systems analysis, evaluation, design, integration, documentation, and implementation of very complex application that require a thorough knowledge of administrative, and technical skills.  Directs and participates in all phases of system development with emphasis on planning, analysis, evaluation, integration, testing and acceptance phases (IV&V and DT&E). Applies higher-level business or technical principles and methods to very difficult technical problems to arrive at automated engineering solution.  Prepares and develops requirements for presentations and briefings as required by assigned mission, and delivers those presentation and briefings as required. Designs and prepares technical reports and related documentation, and makes charts and graphs to record results. May be required to serve as Project Leader.  Responsible for ensuring the quality and services delivered for particular task(s) for which this skill is performing the Project Leader position.
